*The Future of Proactive Fleet Management*












Integration of AI-powered computer vision and crowdsourced video data to
monitor fleets, road conditions, and driver behavior in logistics is need
of the hour.



Unlike traditional GPS-only tracking, a dashcam uses *visual intelligence *=
to
provide real-time "eyes on the ground" for its user.


What=E2=80=99s New?


Dashcam Integration in "Fleets" and "Trace" provides real-time visibility
(location and video).




   - Live Video Streaming

   The feature allows fleet managers to maintain continuous ground-level
   visibility during high-risk maneuvers, emergency situations, or complex
   last-mile deliveries, ensuring driver safety and cargo security.


   - Dual-Channel "Front & Back" Visibility

   This integration now utilizes *Dual-View Dashcams* that capture two
   simultaneous perspectives:
   -

      *Road-Facing (Front):* Monitors traffic, road conditions (potholes),
      and potential collision threats.
      -

      *Cabin-Facing (Back):* Monitors driver behavior and can also check on
      high-value cargo inside the vehicle.



